HEADWORD: Taurylic
<hw>Tau*ryl"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>taurus</ets> a bull + E. phen<ets>ylic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, an acid found of
